<p><em>Journal for New Narratives in the History of Philosophy</em> (<em>JNNHP</em>) is a new, online, open-access, peer-reviewed journal.<span id="more-54561"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class=" wp-image-54562 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/journal-new-narratives-history-philosophy-jnnhp.png" alt="" width="585" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/journal-new-narratives-history-philosophy-jnnhp.png 821w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/journal-new-narratives-history-philosophy-jnnhp-300x205.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/journal-new-narratives-history-philosophy-jnnhp-768x525.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/journal-new-narratives-history-philosophy-jnnhp-400x273.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px" /></p>
<p>The journal&#8217;s focus is &#8220;leading-edge research relating to new narratives in any period in the history of philosophy [and] discussion of and scholarship on diverse, underrepresented, and non-canonical approaches, themes, and figures in a wide variety of world philosophical traditions.&#8221;</p>
<p>The editors write:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><em>Our goal is to provide a platform for philosophical research that contributes to the diversification and broadening of the history of philosophy. In addition to publishing groundbreaking scholarship in the form of articles, we also highlight new scholarly translations, transcriptions, and digital editions of important but neglected or underappreciated works. Our journal aims to be international in scope. </em></p>
<p>The journal&#8217;s editor-in-chief is <a href="https://www.uoguelph.ca/arts/philosophy/people/patricia-sheridan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Patricia Sheridan</a> (University of Guelph).</p>
<p>JNNHP published articles written in English or French. There are no submission fees. The journal uses double-anonymous review. Articles are published on a rolling basis, gathered in annual volumes.</p>
<p>Its first articles will be appearing soon.</p>
<p>You can learn more about the journal at <a href="https://journal.lib.uoguelph.ca/index.php/nnhp/index" target="_blank" rel="noopener">its website</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/08/11/new-journal-for-new-narratives-in-the-history-of-philosophy/">New: Journal for New Narratives in the History of Philosophy</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>